requirements.process:
0x0 "Standby" Debug Message used for informing the status of system in StandBy Mode
0x2 "Enable power module" Debug Message used for informing the status of the system working on HV and enables the converter power module
0x3 "PrechargeLS_ClosePrechargeCtt" Debug Message used for informing the status of Close the precharge contactors
0x4 "PrechargeLS_CloseSolidStateSw" Debug Message used for informing the status of Close the solid state switch on 400V side DC Link;
0x5 "PrechargeLS_OpenPrechargeCtt" Debug Message used for informing the status of Open the precharge contactors;
0x6 "Normal" Debug Message used for informing the status of system working at normal condition.
0x7 "Shutdown_DisablePM" Debug Message used for informing the status of Disable the converter power module;
0x8 "Shutdown_EnableAD400V" Debug Message used for informing the status of Actively discharge 400V side DC Link;
0x9 "Shutdown_DisableAD400V" Debug Message used for informing the status of Disable active discharge on 400V side DC Link;
0xA "Shutdown_OpenSolidStateSw" Debug Message used for informing the status of Open the solid state switch on the 400V side;
0xB "Faulty_OpenSolidStateSw" Debug Message used for informing the status of Open the solid state switch on the 400V side;
0xC "Faulty_Enable400VAD" Debug Message used for informing the status of Actively discharge 400V side DC Link;
0xD "Faulty_Disable400VAD" Debug Message used for informing the status of Disable active discharge on 400V side DC Link;
0xE "Faulty_DisablePM" Debug Message used for informing the status of Disable the converter power module;
0X0F "FaultyUnlatch_ClearPM" Debug Message used for informing the status of Command the converter power module to clear fault.
0x10 "FaultyUnlatch_ClearSys" Debug Message used for informing the status of Command to unlatch the main controller faults.

The HVDCDC shall enable the converter power module if the following conditions are checked and fulfilled:
- The 800V side DC link voltage is greater than 480V (HVDCDC_CAL);
- The EDSU command NHVDCDCCommand == 0x1 "Enable" is received;
- The converter power module is initialised and the communication is established;
- No level 2 fault present.

The HVDCDC shall enable the converter power module if the following conditions are checked and fulfilled:
- The 800V side DC link voltage is greater than 480V (HVDCDC_CAL);
- The EDSU command NHVDCDCCommand == 0x1 "Enable" is received;
- The converter power module is initialised and the communication is established;
- No level 2 fault present;
The HVDCDC shall transit to "Enable power module" state and set NHVDCDCStatus = 0x2 Enable power module.
The HVDCDC shall set NHVDCDCStatusDebug = 0x2 Enable power module.

requirements.outputs:
Disable_power_module.
Disable the converter power module;
NHVDCDCStatusDebug = 0xE "Faulty_DisablePM"
